32namespace cricket {
33
34struct IceTransportStats {
35 CandidateStatsList candidate_stats_list;
36 ConnectionInfos connection_infos;
37 // Number of times the selected candidate pair has changed
38 // Initially 0 and 1 once the first candidate pair has been selected.
39 // The counter is increase also when "unselecting" a connection.
40 uint32_t selected_candidate_pair_changes = 0;
41};
42
43typedef std::vector<Candidate> Candidates;
44
45enum IceConnectionState {
46 kIceConnectionConnecting = 0,
47 kIceConnectionFailed,
48 kIceConnectionConnected, // Writable, but still checking one or more
49 // connections
50 kIceConnectionCompleted,
51};
52
53// TODO(deadbeef): Unify with PeerConnectionInterface::IceConnectionState
54// once /talk/ and /webrtc/ are combined, and also switch to ENUM_NAME naming
55// style.
56enum IceGatheringState {
57 kIceGatheringNew = 0,
58 kIceGatheringGathering,
59 kIceGatheringComplete,
60};
61
62enum ContinualGatheringPolicy {
63 // All port allocator sessions will stop after a writable connection is found.
64 GATHER_ONCE = 0,
65 // The most recent port allocator session will keep on running.
66 GATHER_CONTINUALLY,
67};
68
69// ICE Nomination mode.
70enum class NominationMode {
71 REGULAR, // Nominate once per ICE restart (Not implemented yet).
72 AGGRESSIVE, // Nominate every connection except that it will behave as if
73 // REGULAR when the remote is an ICE-LITE endpoint.
74 SEMI_AGGRESSIVE // Our current implementation of the nomination algorithm.
75 // The details are described in P2PTransportChannel.
76};
77
78// Utility method that checks if various required Candidate fields are filled in
79// and contain valid values. If conditions are not met, an RTCError with the
80// appropriated error number and description is returned. If the configuration
81// is valid RTCError::OK() is returned.
82webrtc::RTCError VerifyCandidate(const Candidate& cand);
83
84// Runs through a list of cricket::Candidate instances and calls VerifyCandidate
85// for each one, stopping on the first error encounted and returning that error
86// value if so. On success returns RTCError::OK().
87webrtc::RTCError VerifyCandidates(const Candidates& candidates);
88
89// Information about ICE configuration.
90// TODO(deadbeef): Use absl::optional to represent unset values, instead of
91// -1.
92struct IceConfig {
93 // The ICE connection receiving timeout value in milliseconds.
94 absl::optional<int> receiving_timeout;
95 // Time interval in milliseconds to ping a backup connection when the ICE
96 // channel is strongly connected.
97 absl::optional<int> backup_connection_ping_interval;
98
99 ContinualGatheringPolicy continual_gathering_policy = GATHER_ONCE;
100
101 bool gather_continually() const {
102 return continual_gathering_policy == GATHER_CONTINUALLY;
103 }
104
105 // Whether we should prioritize Relay/Relay candidate when nothing
106 // is writable yet.
107 bool prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs = false;
108
109 // Writable connections are pinged at a slower rate once stablized.
110 absl::optional<int> stable_writable_connection_ping_interval;
111
112 // If set to true, this means the ICE transport should presume TURN-to-TURN
113 // candidate pairs will succeed, even before a binding response is received.
114 bool presume_writable_when_fully_relayed = false;
115
116 // If true, after the ICE transport type (as the candidate filter used by the
117 // port allocator) is changed such that new types of ICE candidates are
118 // allowed by the new filter, e.g. from CF_RELAY to CF_ALL, candidates that
119 // have been gathered by the ICE transport but filtered out and not signaled
120 // to the upper layers, will be surfaced.
121 bool surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed = false;
122
123 // Interval to check on all networks and to perform ICE regathering on any
124 // active network having no connection on it.
125 absl::optional<int> regather_on_failed_networks_interval;
126
127 // The time period in which we will not switch the selected connection
128 // when a new connection becomes receiving but the selected connection is not
129 // in case that the selected connection may become receiving soon.
130 absl::optional<int> receiving_switching_delay;
131
132 // TODO(honghaiz): Change the default to regular nomination.
133 // Default nomination mode if the remote does not support renomination.
134 NominationMode default_nomination_mode = NominationMode::SEMI_AGGRESSIVE;
135
136 // The interval in milliseconds at which ICE checks (STUN pings) will be sent
137 // for a candidate pair when it is both writable and receiving (strong
138 // connectivity). This parameter overrides the default value given by
139 // |STRONG_PING_INTERVAL| in p2ptransport.h if set.
140 absl::optional<int> ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity;
141 // The interval in milliseconds at which ICE checks (STUN pings) will be sent
142 // for a candidate pair when it is either not writable or not receiving (weak
143 // connectivity). This parameter overrides the default value given by
144 // |WEAK_PING_INTERVAL| in p2ptransport.h if set.
145 absl::optional<int> ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity;
146 // ICE checks (STUN pings) will not be sent at higher rate (lower interval)
147 // than this, no matter what other settings there are.
148 // Measure in milliseconds.
149 //
150 // Note that this parameter overrides both the above check intervals for
151 // candidate pairs with strong or weak connectivity, if either of the above
152 // interval is shorter than the min interval.
153 absl::optional<int> ice_check_min_interval;
154 // The min time period for which a candidate pair must wait for response to
155 // connectivity checks before it becomes unwritable. This parameter
156 // overrides the default value given by |CONNECTION_WRITE_CONNECT_TIMEOUT|
157 // in port.h if set, when determining the writability of a candidate pair.
158 absl::optional<int> ice_unwritable_timeout;
159
160 // The min number of connectivity checks that a candidate pair must sent
161 // without receiving response before it becomes unwritable. This parameter
162 // overrides the default value given by |CONNECTION_WRITE_CONNECT_FAILURES| in
163 // port.h if set, when determining the writability of a candidate pair.
164 absl::optional<int> ice_unwritable_min_checks;
165
166 // The min time period for which a candidate pair must wait for response to
167 // connectivity checks it becomes inactive. This parameter overrides the
168 // default value given by |CONNECTION_WRITE_TIMEOUT| in port.h if set, when
169 // determining the writability of a candidate pair.
170 absl::optional<int> ice_inactive_timeout;
171
172 // The interval in milliseconds at which STUN candidates will resend STUN
173 // binding requests to keep NAT bindings open.
174 absl::optional<int> stun_keepalive_interval;
175
176 absl::optional<rtc::AdapterType> network_preference;
177
178 IceConfig();
179 IceConfig(int receiving_timeout_ms,
180 int backup_connection_ping_interval,
181 ContinualGatheringPolicy gathering_policy,
182 bool prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs,
183 int stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_ms,
184 bool presume_writable_when_fully_relayed,
185 int regather_on_failed_networks_interval_ms,
186 int receiving_switching_delay_ms);
187 ~IceConfig();
188
189 // Helper getters for parameters with implementation-specific default value.
190 // By convention, parameters with default value are represented by
191 // absl::optional and setting a parameter to null restores its default value.
192 int receiving_timeout_or_default() const;
193 int backup_connection_ping_interval_or_default() const;
194 int stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_or_default() const;
195 int regather_on_failed_networks_interval_or_default() const;
196 int receiving_switching_delay_or_default() const;
197 int ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity_or_default() const;
198 int ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity_or_default() const;
199 int ice_check_min_interval_or_default() const;
200 int ice_unwritable_timeout_or_default() const;
201 int ice_unwritable_min_checks_or_default() const;
202 int ice_inactive_timeout_or_default() const;
203 int stun_keepalive_interval_or_default() const;
204};

206// TODO(zhihuang): Replace this with
207// PeerConnectionInterface::IceConnectionState.
208enum class IceTransportState {
209 STATE_INIT,
210 STATE_CONNECTING, // Will enter this state once a connection is created
211 STATE_COMPLETED,
212 STATE_FAILED
213};
214
215// TODO(zhihuang): Remove this once it's no longer used in
216// remoting/protocol/libjingle_transport_factory.cc
217enum IceProtocolType {
218 ICEPROTO_RFC5245 // Standard RFC 5245 version of ICE.
219};
220
221// IceTransportInternal is an internal abstract class that does ICE.
222// Once the public interface is supported,
223// (https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/#rtcicetransport)
224// the IceTransportInterface will be split from this class.
225class RTC_EXPORT IceTransportInternal : public rtc::PacketTransportInternal {
226 public:
227 IceTransportInternal();
228 ~IceTransportInternal() override;
229
230 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/9308): Remove GetState once all uses have been
231 // migrated to GetIceTransportState.
232 virtual IceTransportState GetState() const = 0;
233 virtual webrtc::IceTransportState GetIceTransportState() const = 0;
234
235 virtual int component() const = 0;
236
237 virtual IceRole GetIceRole() const = 0;
238
239 virtual void SetIceRole(IceRole role) = 0;
240
241 virtual void SetIceTiebreaker(uint64_t tiebreaker) = 0;
242
243 // TODO(zhihuang): Remove this once it's no longer called in
244 // remoting/protocol/libjingle_transport_factory.cc
245 virtual void SetIceProtocolType(IceProtocolType type) {}
246
247 virtual void SetIceCredentials(const std::string& ice_ufrag,
248 const std::string& ice_pwd);
249
250 virtual void SetRemoteIceCredentials(const std::string& ice_ufrag,
251 const std::string& ice_pwd);
252
253 // The ufrag and pwd in |ice_params| must be set
254 // before candidate gathering can start.
255 virtual void SetIceParameters(const IceParameters& ice_params) = 0;
256
257 virtual void SetRemoteIceParameters(const IceParameters& ice_params) = 0;
258
259 virtual void SetRemoteIceMode(IceMode mode) = 0;
260
261 virtual void SetIceConfig(const IceConfig& config) = 0;
262
263 // Start gathering candidates if not already started, or if an ICE restart
264 // occurred.
265 virtual void MaybeStartGathering() = 0;
266
267 virtual void AddRemoteCandidate(const Candidate& candidate) = 0;
268
269 virtual void RemoveRemoteCandidate(const Candidate& candidate) = 0;
270
271 virtual void RemoveAllRemoteCandidates() = 0;
272
273 virtual IceGatheringState gathering_state() const = 0;
274
275 // Returns the current stats for this connection.
276 virtual bool GetStats(IceTransportStats* ice_transport_stats) = 0;
277
278 // Returns RTT estimate over the currently active connection, or an empty
279 // absl::optional if there is none.
280 virtual absl::optional<int> GetRttEstimate() = 0;
281
282 // TODO(qingsi): Remove this method once Chrome does not depend on it anymore.
283 virtual const Connection* selected_connection() const = 0;
284
285 // Returns the selected candidate pair, or an empty absl::optional if there is
286 // none.
287 virtual absl::optional<const CandidatePair> GetSelectedCandidatePair()
288 const = 0;
289
290 sigslot::signal1<IceTransportInternal*> SignalGatheringState;
291
292 // Handles sending and receiving of candidates.
293 sigslot::signal2<IceTransportInternal*, const Candidate&>
294 SignalCandidateGathered;
295
296 sigslot::signal2<IceTransportInternal*, const IceCandidateErrorEvent&>
297 SignalCandidateError;
298
299 sigslot::signal2<IceTransportInternal*, const Candidates&>
300 SignalCandidatesRemoved;
301
302 // Deprecated by PacketTransportInternal::SignalNetworkRouteChanged.
303 // This signal occurs when there is a change in the way that packets are
304 // being routed, i.e. to a different remote location. The candidate
305 // indicates where and how we are currently sending media.
306 // TODO(zhihuang): Update the Chrome remoting to use the new
307 // SignalNetworkRouteChanged.
308 sigslot::signal2<IceTransportInternal*, const Candidate&> SignalRouteChange;
309
310 sigslot::signal1<const cricket::CandidatePairChangeEvent&>
311 SignalCandidatePairChanged;
312
313 // Invoked when there is conflict in the ICE role between local and remote
314 // agents.
315 sigslot::signal1<IceTransportInternal*> SignalRoleConflict;
316
317 // Emitted whenever the transport state changed.
318 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/9308): Remove once all uses have migrated to the new
319 // IceTransportState.
320 sigslot::signal1<IceTransportInternal*> SignalStateChanged;
321
322 // Emitted whenever the new standards-compliant transport state changed.
323 sigslot::signal1<IceTransportInternal*> SignalIceTransportStateChanged;
324
325 // Invoked when the transport is being destroyed.
326 sigslot::signal1<IceTransportInternal*> SignalDestroyed;
327};
328
329} // namespace cricket
